Part II — Economic Systems

Methodological Note on Energy‑Information Analysis Sections:

The Energy‑Information Analysis sections that follow apply the ℳ framework to each domain. In some cases (production, governance, finance), the application can be made partially quantitative: we can estimate efficiencies, compare trade‑offs, and identify scaling relationships. In others (art, religion), the framework serves an analogical function—illuminating structural parallels without quantitative precision. The reader should distinguish these modes accordingly. The framework's power lies not in forcing all phenomena into a single metric, but in revealing where energy and information truly are the governing currencies—and where they are not.

